[thinking] I'm thinking about using ApplicationContextRunner with user settings and IntegrationAutoConfiguration. I want to define an IntegrationFlow from an input channel transform, using MessagingTemplate for send/receive. I’m curious if @EnableIntegration from auto config registers necessary processors. This could test if the auto-configuration enables the Spring Integration infrastructure properly. I need to make sure there's no background process, considering DirectChannel is synchronous. I wonder about testing in a native image context and whether it requires reflection with @Configuration classes.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Configuring Spring Integration Flow**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m looking at the existing tests that use ApplicationContextRunner without any custom annotated config, and it seems fine since Spring AOT isn’t involved. For defining a simple integration flow, I'll use a static configuration class with a `Configuration` annotation and specify `proxyBeanMethods = false`. The `uppercaseFlow` bean transforms input to uppercase and sends it to the output channel. I'm unsure if the input channel will be auto-created. I'll use MessagingTemplate to send a message to the input channel and ensure proper imports for all necessary classes. But does auto-config require @EnableIntegration?
[thinking] 
